question: Which dish, consisting of toast, bacon, poached egg and Hollandaise sauce, is named after a 19th century New York stockbroker?
vanilla_rag_result: The dish you are referring to is Eggs Benedict. It was created when Lemuel Benedict, a retired Wall Street stockbroker, ordered "buttered toast, poached eggs, crisp bacon, and a hooker of hollandaise" at the Waldorf Hotel in 1894.
